author: COMSOL
description: This is the model of a generic ear canal simulator (or coupler). The real life couplers are used for simulating the acoustics of a standardized human ear canal and can be used for measurements on all sorts of devices. They are widely used in the hearing aid industry and also as ear canals on all sorts of acoustic manikins for recording 3D sound. The model results are compared with the IEC standard curves and with results obtained with a pure pressure acoustics model.
